    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a mechanically sound F80-generation M3 featuring the S55 3.0L twin-turbocharged inline-six. This powerplant utilizes a closed-deck block and a forged crankshaft to maintain structural integrity under high boost pressures. Power is delivered through a 7-speed M-DCT dual-clutch transmission, paired with an Active M Differential that optimizes torque distribution across the rear axle. The suspension retains its factory-spec damping characteristics, complemented by a CFRP strut tower brace for enhanced front-end turn-in precision. The vehicle exhibits excellent thermal management with no signs of heat soak or fluid egress. While the exterior shows minor aerodynamic wear consistent with road use, the drivetrain remains robust with a linear power delivery and crisp gear synchronization. This is a driver-focused example ready for technical scrutiny.",
